The paper deals with approximation algorithms and hardness results for various cut problems, which are fundamental problems in theoretical computer science. The techniques used in the paper involve combinatorial algorithms, LP relaxations, and region growing lemmas, which are commonly used in the areas of algorithms, discrete mathematics, computational geometry, game theory, and complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
